adjectives.description: starched (comparative more starched, superlative most starched)

entries.meaning: Of a garment: having had starch applied.
Stiff, formal, rigid; prim and proper.
examples: Does the Gospel any where prescribe a starched squeezed Countenance, a stiff formal Gait, a Singularity of Manners and Habit, or any affected Modes of Speech, different from the reasonable Part of Mankind?

entries.meaning: simple past tense and past participle of starch
